<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Philomel" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Philomel,</orth> 1) the nightingale: <bibl n="shak. luc 1079" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1079</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 1079" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1079</bibl> <bibl n="shak. son 102.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 102, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.2.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 2, 13</bibl>.<lb />2) the daughter of Pandion, ravished by Tereus, who cut her tongue afterwards, to conceal his crime: <bibl n="shak. luc 1128" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1128</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.43" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 43</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.4.43" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 43</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.1.47" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.2.47" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.2.47" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2</bibl> <bibl n="shak. cym 2.2.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 2, 46</bibl>.
